body:
I stumbled upon this while working on my [cargo cache](https://github.com/matthiaskrgr/cargo-cache) crate.
````rustc 1.30.0-nightly (721913067 2018-08-26)````
Essentially I cast a negative ````int```` to ````usize```` and pass it to ````String.repeat()```` but there is no compiler warning and no backtrace when crashing, even in debug mode.

````rust
fn pad_strings(indent_lvl: i8, beginning: &str) -> String {
    const MAX_WIDTH: i8 = 37;
    let len_padding: i8 = (MAX_WIDTH + indent_lvl * 2) - (beginning.len() as i8);
    println!("padding: {}", len_padding);
    let mut formatted_line = beginning.to_string();
    // here we cast a negative value to usize
    formatted_line.push_str(&String::from(" ").repeat(len_padding as usize));
    formatted_line
}

fn main() {
        pad_strings(2, "Size of 1938493989 crate source checkouts: ").to_string();
}
````
when running:
````
   Compiling cargo-cache v0.1.0 (file:///home/matthias/vcs/github/cargo-cache)
    Finished dev [unoptimized + debuginfo] target(s) in 0.26s
     Running `target/debug/cargo-cache`
padding: -2
memory allocation of 18446744073709551614 bytes failed[1]    18030 abort (core dumped)  cargo --color=always run
````

Debugging this would have been MUCH easier with a proper backtrace :)
